# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: Other | Scene: WanderingTheCamp
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Sarah woke up. Outside, she could hear the camp had already come alive."
    new "Sarah woke up. Outside, she could hear the camp had already come alive."

    old "Nobody else was left, Ephraim and Caleb had already started their day. Alone again."
    new "Nobody else was left, Ephraim and Caleb had already started their day. Alone again."

    old "Sarah began to think about last night. Watching Caleb and Ephraim fuck had been unexpected. So too had been her reaction."
    new "Sarah began to think about last night. Watching Caleb and Ephraim fuck had been unexpected. So too had been her reaction."

    old "She could feel herself growing hotter, just remembering."
    new "She could feel herself growing hotter, just remembering."

    old "Sarah shook her head. She needed to focus, she couldn't lay in bed masturbating all day."
    new "Sarah shook her head. She needed to focus, she couldn't lay in bed masturbating all day."

    old "Sarah stretched her arms. This was not the kind of bed she was used to."
    new "Sarah stretched her arms. This was not the kind of bed she was used to."

    old "Sarah got out of bed and began to get dressed."
    new "Sarah got out of bed and began to get dressed."

    old "With most of her clothes lost because of Kate, she was forced to keep wearing the same dress."
    new "With most of her clothes lost because of Kate, she was forced to keep wearing the same dress."

    old "Kate..."
    new "Kate..."

    old "Sarah still had trouble to reconcile the Kate she thought she knew, versus what Kate had done to her."
    new "Sarah still had trouble to reconcile the Kate she thought she knew, versus what Kate had done to her."

    old "Sarah left the tent. The ambiance of the mercenary camp washed over her. It's smells, sounds, the structured chaos."
    new "Sarah left the tent. The ambiance of the mercenary camp washed over her. It's smells, sounds, the structured chaos."

    old "So different from the castle in which she grew up."
    new "So different from the castle in which she grew up."

    old "Sarah knew this world was different. There were different rules. She had to be careful. Unlike back home, her station offered her little protection."
    new "Sarah knew this world was different. There were different rules. She had to be careful. Unlike back home, her station offered her little protection."

    old "Quite the opposite, she realized, if people knew she was a princess, who knew what they would do..."
    new "Quite the opposite, she realized, if people knew she was a princess, who knew what they would do..."

    old "Sarah had made her plan, she would go to the harbor and ask around. See if there was a ship heading back to Rosanna."
    new "Sarah had made her plan, she would go to the harbor and ask around. See if there was a ship heading back to Rosanna."

    old "She knew it wasn't much of a plan, but then again, right now, she didn't have many options."
    new "She knew it wasn't much of a plan, but then again, right now, she didn't have many options."

    old "Walking through the camp, heading to the exit, Sarah was lost in thought."
    new "Walking through the camp, heading to the exit, Sarah was lost in thought."

    old "She suddenly felt a sharp pang against her shin, followed by her losing her balance."
    new "She suddenly felt a sharp pang against her shin, followed by her losing her balance."

    old "As Sarah tumbled across the floor, getting dust in her eyes and on her dress, she heard the noise of metal clattering."
    new "As Sarah tumbled across the floor, getting dust in her eyes and on her dress, she heard the noise of metal clattering."

    old "She looked up, trying to see what had happened."
    new "She looked up, trying to see what had happened."

    old "Instead, she felt herself getting pulled up to her feet with a force stronger than any she had never experienced in her life."
    new "Instead, she felt herself getting pulled up to her feet with a force stronger than any she had never experienced in her life."

    old "She felt the titanic power of the hand, clenched around her upper arm, holding her up."
    new "She felt the titanic power of the hand, clenched around her upper arm, holding her up."

    old "Inches away from her face, she saw the orc's furious gaze."
    new "Inches away from her face, she saw the orc's furious gaze."

    old "Look what you've done, you stupid girl!"
    new "Look what you've done, you stupid girl!"

    old "The orc barked at her."
    new "The orc barked at her."

    old "Sarah saw, on the ground behind the orc, a plate and some cooking utensils."
    new "Sarah saw, on the ground behind the orc, a plate and some cooking utensils."

    old "She began to realize that, lost in thought, she had knocked over the orc's table, spilling his food onto the floor."
    new "She began to realize that, lost in thought, she had knocked over the orc's table, spilling his food onto the floor."

    old "I'm so sorry..."
    new "I'm so sorry..."

    old "Her voice was weak, the orc radiated a menace that she had never experienced before. She truly believed he might kill her over it."
    new "Her voice was weak, the orc radiated a menace that she had never experienced before. She truly believed he might kill her over it."

    old "Sarah slipped from his grasp and crawled across the floor. She hastily began collecting the plate and everything else she had knocked over."
    new "Sarah slipped from his grasp and crawled across the floor. She hastily began collecting the plate and everything else she had knocked over."

    old "She hurried to put it all back on the table. She kept apologizing as she did, hoping the orc would spare her."
    new "She hurried to put it all back on the table. She kept apologizing as she did, hoping the orc would spare her."

    old "Sarah watched as the orc fell back in his chair, next to his table."
    new "Sarah watched as the orc fell back in his chair, next to his table."

    old "She watched him, his eyes still full of anger, but seemingly less than before."
    new "She watched him, his eyes still full of anger, but seemingly less than before."

    old "His arms were like logs, even his legs were large and muscular."
    new "His arms were like logs, even his legs were large and muscular."

    old "The orc waved his hands, dismissing her without looking at Sarah."
    new "The orc waved his hands, dismissing her without looking at Sarah."

    old "Go, the damage is already done!"
    new "Go, the damage is already done!"

    old "But gods help you girl if you do something like this again!"
    new "But gods help you girl if you do something like this again!"

    old "Sarah, grasped at her new lease on life and leapt up to her feet."
    new "Sarah, grasped at her new lease on life and leapt up to her feet."

    old "She bowed to the orc, apologizing, as she simultaneously backed away."
    new "She bowed to the orc, apologizing, as she simultaneously backed away."

    old "I'm sorry, I'm sorry, I'm sorry."
    new "I'm sorry, I'm sorry, I'm sorry."

    old "Get away, she thought, just keep walking. He's letting you live."
    new "Get away, she thought, just keep walking. He's letting you live."

    old "Sarah turned the corner and leaned against the wall, breathing heavily."
    new "Sarah turned the corner and leaned against the wall, breathing heavily."

    old "A moment of inattention, and she had almost paid for it dearly."
    new "A moment of inattention, and she had almost paid for it dearly."

    old "She had to get out of here."
    new "She had to get out of here."

    old "Sarah made her way to the camp's gate, marching as fast as she could."
    new "Sarah made her way to the camp's gate, marching as fast as she could."

    old "After this, down the road, past the shops, into the harbor. She tried to remember the path that Kate had dragged her along."
    new "After this, down the road, past the shops, into the harbor. She tried to remember the path that Kate had dragged her along."

    old "A man blocked her path."
    new "A man blocked her path."

    old "Camp Guard\" \"Hold on there."
    new "Camp Guard\" \"Hold on there."

    old "The man was large, easily blocking Sarah from getting past him. He pushed her back."
    new "The man was large, easily blocking Sarah from getting past him. He pushed her back."

    old "I need to leave, I have to get to the harbor."
    new "I need to leave, I have to get to the harbor."

    old "The camp guard shook his head."
    new "The camp guard shook his head."

    old "Camp Guard\" \"You're not going anywhere. Orders, straight from Vaelen himself."
    new "Camp Guard\" \"You're not going anywhere. Orders, straight from Vaelen himself."

    old "Sarah was stunned."
    new "Sarah was stunned."

    old "You don't even know who I am, just let me go, please."
    new "You don't even know who I am, just let me go, please."

    old "She pleaded with the guard."
    new "She pleaded with the guard."

    old "The guard shook his head again. He planted his feet firmer, as if to reinforce his point."
    new "The guard shook his head again. He planted his feet firmer, as if to reinforce his point."

    old "Camp Guard\" \"Vaelen told me himself, keep the blonde girl in the pretty dress from leaving."
    new "Camp Guard\" \"Vaelen told me himself, keep the blonde girl in the pretty dress from leaving."

    old "Camp Guard\" \"It might surprise you to learn, but there aren't a lot of people here matching that description."
    new "Camp Guard\" \"It might surprise you to learn, but there aren't a lot of people here matching that description."

    old "Sarah thought about what she could do, but there was no way she was getting past the guard."
    new "Sarah thought about what she could do, but there was no way she was getting past the guard."

    old "She turned around and began to walk back into the camp."
    new "She turned around and began to walk back into the camp."

    old "Sarah had lost the speed in her step. There was nowhere for her to walk to, other then back to the tent."
    new "Sarah had lost the speed in her step. There was nowhere for her to walk to, other then back to the tent."

    old "She went back the way she came."
    new "She went back the way she came."

    old "She passed the orc, and quickly glanced in his direction."
    new "She passed the orc, and quickly glanced in his direction."

    old "The orc met her eyes."
    new "The orc met her eyes."

    old "Sarah turned her eyes back to the ground, hoping to avoid his wrath a second time."
    new "Sarah turned her eyes back to the ground, hoping to avoid his wrath a second time."

    old "She took a wide berth around his table."
    new "She took a wide berth around his table."

    old "Sarah eventually made her way back to the tent."
    new "Sarah eventually made her way back to the tent."

    old "To her surprise, the flap to the tent was thrown aside, and Kate came storming out."
    new "To her surprise, the flap to the tent was thrown aside, and Kate came storming out."

    old "Sarah! Are you ok? I heard about you and Atilla..."
    new "Sarah! Are you ok? I heard about you and Atilla..."

    old "Sarah looked confused, for a moment forgetting what had transpired between them."
    new "Sarah looked confused, for a moment forgetting what had transpired between them."

    old "Atilla?"
    new "Atilla?"

    old "The orc, that vile creature. Did he hurt you?"
    new "The orc, that vile creature. Did he hurt you?"

    old "Sarah felt her upper arm. It was bruised, but other than that, she was more scared than hurt."
    new "Sarah felt her upper arm. It was bruised, but other than that, she was more scared than hurt."

    old "Kate embraced Sarah."
    new "Kate embraced Sarah."

    old "Thank the gods, I was so worried that he would hurt you."
    new "Thank the gods, I was so worried that he would hurt you."

    old "Sarah suddenly pushed Kate away."
    new "Sarah suddenly pushed Kate away."

    old "Only one person in this camp has hurt me..."
    new "Only one person in this camp has hurt me..."

    old "Sarah stared daggers at Kate."
    new "Sarah stared daggers at Kate."

    old "Kate looked away in shame."
    new "Kate looked away in shame."

    old "Usually, Kate's voice was strong, but now, it was soft and weak."
    new "Usually, Kate's voice was strong, but now, it was soft and weak."

    old "What I did to you, Sarah..."
    new "What I did to you, Sarah..."

    old "Why did you do it, Kate? I thought we were friends."
    new "Why did you do it, Kate? I thought we were friends."

    old "When you made love to me, after the funeral...did it mean nothing to you?"
    new "When you made love to me, after the funeral...did it mean nothing to you?"

    old "Kate sagged down, sitting down by the entrance to the tent."
    new "Kate sagged down, sitting down by the entrance to the tent."

    old "Sarah...will you let me explain?"
    new "Sarah...will you let me explain?"

    old "I want to know why you did it."
    new "I want to know why you did it."

    old "Sarah fights every urge to tell Kate to leave, and nods."
    new "Sarah fights every urge to tell Kate to leave, and nods."

    old "The two old friends go into the tent together."
    new "The two old friends go into the tent together."

    old "They sit down together on the same bed."
    new "They sit down together on the same bed."

    old "They're quiet for a long time. Kate finally breaks the silence."
    new "They're quiet for a long time. Kate finally breaks the silence."

    old "I've tried to be honest with you, Sarah. As honest as I could be."
    new "I've tried to be honest with you, Sarah. As honest as I could be."

    old "But when I told you about my life after running away, there were a lot of things I didn't tell you about."
    new "But when I told you about my life after running away, there were a lot of things I didn't tell you about."

    old "Kate pulls her knees to her chest."
    new "Kate pulls her knees to her chest."

    old "This world...it can be very cruel to a girl, all alone."
    new "This world...it can be very cruel to a girl, all alone."

    old "To survive, I had to do a lot of things that...I didn't want to tell you about."
    new "To survive, I had to do a lot of things that...I didn't want to tell you about."

    old "For a long time, my life was pretty miserable. Everywhere I went, I was alone. People would be so cruel to me..."
    new "For a long time, my life was pretty miserable. Everywhere I went, I was alone. People would be so cruel to me..."

    old "Sarah noticed Kate turning more quiet, more inward."
    new "Sarah noticed Kate turning more quiet, more inward."

    old "Sarah surprised herself when she found her own hand, moving across her friend's back, comforting her."
    new "Sarah surprised herself when she found her own hand, moving across her friend's back, comforting her."

    old "Why do I still love her, Sarah thought to herself. She felt her hatred for Kate slip out of her fingers."
    new "Why do I still love her, Sarah thought to herself. She felt her hatred for Kate slip out of her fingers."

    old "I tried to be strong, but some days...the pain was just too much."
    new "I tried to be strong, but some days...the pain was just too much."

    old "I developed ways of dealing with that pain..."
    new "I developed ways of dealing with that pain..."

    old "There were a few things, like drugs, but above all, alcohol."
    new "There were a few things, like drugs, but above all, alcohol."

    old "Kate paused again, staring off into a memory that Sarah could not reach."
    new "Kate paused again, staring off into a memory that Sarah could not reach."

    old "It numbed the pain, and it let me survive when things got too bad. But over time, the cure got worse than the disease."
    new "It numbed the pain, and it let me survive when things got too bad. But over time, the cure got worse than the disease."

    old "I found myself blacked out in alleys, no idea how I got there."
    new "I found myself blacked out in alleys, no idea how I got there."

    old "Kate stared at Sarah, tears were running down Kate's face."
    new "Kate stared at Sarah, tears were running down Kate's face."

    old "I was going to die there, Sarah, I knew it in my heart back then. One day I would black out in some alley, and someone would cut my throat or I would freeze to death, I just knew it."
    new "I was going to die there, Sarah, I knew it in my heart back then. One day I would black out in some alley, and someone would cut my throat or I would freeze to death, I just knew it."

    old "And this world would throw me away like garbage."
    new "And this world would throw me away like garbage."

    old "Sarah embraced her friend, who had now opened up to her."
    new "Sarah embraced her friend, who had now opened up to her."

    old "That's when they found me, when Vaelen found me. They pulled me from the void and they gave me a life. A life I always wanted."
    new "That's when they found me, when Vaelen found me. They pulled me from the void and they gave me a life. A life I always wanted."

    old "But those old wounds...they never fully healed. This disease, the addiction, it's inside of me in a way I can't explain."
    new "But those old wounds...they never fully healed. This disease, the addiction, it's inside of me in a way I can't explain."

    old "What you saw, what I did to you...that's not who I am...or...who I want to be...I mean."
    new "What you saw, what I did to you...that's not who I am...or...who I want to be...I mean."

    old "Sarah reached out. She clasped Kate's head between her hands."
    new "Sarah reached out. She clasped Kate's head between her hands."

    old "Sarah didn't know why, only that she needed to. She leaned in and kissed Kate."
    new "Sarah didn't know why, only that she needed to. She leaned in and kissed Kate."

    old "Kate seemed as stunned as Sarah."
    new "Kate seemed as stunned as Sarah."

    old "Ooh, Kate..."
    new "Ooh, Kate..."

    old "Tears kept streaming down Kate's face."
    new "Tears kept streaming down Kate's face."

    old "Sarah, I'm so sorry."
    new "Sarah, I'm so sorry."

    old "She was sobbing by now."
    new "She was sobbing by now."

    old "Sarah pulled Kate into a tight embrace, and together the friends fell back into the bed."
    new "Sarah pulled Kate into a tight embrace, and together the friends fell back into the bed."

    old "For what felt like hours, the two remained in a silent embrace, healing wounds of betrayal without speaking."
    new "For what felt like hours, the two remained in a silent embrace, healing wounds of betrayal without speaking."

    old "Sharing pain, without words."
    new "Sharing pain, without words."

    old "In the end, Kate got back up to her feet."
    new "In the end, Kate got back up to her feet."

    old "I know I don't deserve it, but I hope I can earn your forgiveness one day."
    new "I know I don't deserve it, but I hope I can earn your forgiveness one day."

    old "Sarah looked up at her friend."
    new "Sarah looked up at her friend."

    old "There is nothing left to forgive."
    new "There is nothing left to forgive."

    old "Kate bowed her head low."
    new "Kate bowed her head low."

    old "I've spoken to Vaelen about you. We're going to see what we can do. Maybe get you back safe to Rosanna."
    new "I've spoken to Vaelen about you. We're going to see what we can do. Maybe get you back safe to Rosanna."

    old "Kate turns and quickly leaves the tent, hiding her face as she runs off into the camp."
    new "Kate turns and quickly leaves the tent, hiding her face as she runs off into the camp."

    old "There is nothing to explain, leave me alone."
    new "There is nothing to explain, leave me alone."

    old "Kate gets up and walks away. She can't bring herself to face Sarah."
    new "Kate gets up and walks away. She can't bring herself to face Sarah."

    old "Vaelen wants to speak to you."
    new "Vaelen wants to speak to you."

    old "It's the last thing Kate says before she storms off."
    new "It's the last thing Kate says before she storms off."

    old "Sarah goes into the tent and falls down onto the bed."
    new "Sarah goes into the tent and falls down onto the bed."

    old "It's still day, but she can't bring herself to get out of the bed anymore."
    new "It's still day, but she can't bring herself to get out of the bed anymore."

